NAME
	video-overlay (display) - render a vid9p video feed with anti-aliased annotation boxes read from the sibling vision service

INTERFACE
	display (MatrixDisplay + MatrixTicker)

READS
	<mount>/fmt, /frame, /status	the vid9p stream (as video-pane)
	<vision>/boxes	one detection per line: "x0 y0 x1 y1 label...",
			frame pixel coordinates; <vision> is the mount
			with /video/ replaced by /vision/

WRITES
	<mount>/ctl	transport (keys forward, as video-pane)

DESCRIPTION
	video-pane plus an annotation layer: after each frame is
	composited, every box in <vision>/boxes is stroked anti-aliased
	(aadraw, theme accent) with its label above, transformed from
	frame to pane coordinates.  The vision tree is just another 9P
	mount beside the stream (the INFR-277 convention), so anything —
	an ML service, an agent, a host process, sh — can write
	detections and they appear on the live video.  The video-overlay
	crystallisation wires this with transport; demo-overlay.sh feeds
	a synthetic tracker.

SEE ALSO
